{"type": "root", "attrs": {"subtopics_title": "Contexts"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["VEX contexts"], "extent": [0, 17]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Guide to the different contexts in which you can write VEX\nprograms."], "extent": [46, 122]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Unlike C or C++, VEX has different ", {"type": "q", "text": ["contexts"]}, " for which you write programs. These contexts define how the function is to be used."], "extent": [122, 253]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For example, one context is the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["surface"]}, " context. Functions written in this context are used to calculate the color(s) of a surface during rendering. The global variables and functions provided for each context are slightly different."], "extent": [253, 491]}, {"level": 1, "id": "subtopics", "container": true, "type": "subtopics_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [491, 502], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Shading contexts"], "extent": [502, 526], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "shading_contexts", "type": "link", "text": ["common shading context features"], "fullpath": "/vex/contexts/shading_contexts"}, " for information specific to the shading contexts."], "extent": [526, 633]}, {"type": "subtopics_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "subtopics_item", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "displace", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/vex/contexts/displace"}], "role": "item", "extent": [633, 646]}, {"ext": null, "type": "subtopics_item", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "fog", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/vex/contexts/fog"}], "role": "item", "extent": [646, 654]}, {"ext": null, "type": "subtopics_item", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "light", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/vex/con